{"title":"Michelin Pilot BMX Racing Tires borrowing rubber tech from their Road Competition line","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/03/22/michelin-pilot-bmx-racing-tires-borrowing-rubber-tech-from-their-road-competition-line/","date":1616427018000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-3\"></span>Michelin have added two new tires to their BMX Racing line in the form of the Pilot SX ans the Pilot SX Slick. Both tires use rubber sourced from Michelin <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/01/09/michelin-power-tire-range-adds-tubeless-ready-road-time-trial-specific-tires-for-2020/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">competition road bike tires</a>, with tread patterns optimized for different track conditions and ground temperatures.</p><h2>Michelin Pilot SX &amp; Pilot SX Slick</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100404/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-racing-tires.jpg\"><img loading=\"eager\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100404/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-racing-tires.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng%3Awebp%2Fngcb8%2Frs%3Adevice%2Frscb8-1\" alt=\"michelin pilot sx slick bmx racing tires\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100404/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-racing-tires.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100404/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-racing-tires-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100404/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-racing-tires-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100404/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-racing-tires-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100404/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-racing-tires-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100404/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-racing-tires-696x464.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100404/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-racing-tires-1068x712.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100404/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-racing-tires-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\"></a></p><p>The Michelin Pilot SX and Pilot SX Slick BMX Racing tires share a very similar tread pattern to one another, with the Slick option featuring a much shallower tread depth for reduced rolling resistance. It is said to be suitable for racing on hard tracks or in warmer temperatures.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing.jpg\" alt=\"michelin pilot sx slick bmx tire tread pattern\" width=\"1200\" height=\"771\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing-297x191.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing-800x514.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing-120x77.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing-768x493.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing-696x447.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing-1068x686.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing-654x420.jpg 654w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing-297x191.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing-800x514.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing-120x77.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing-768x493.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing-696x447.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing-1068x686.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102549/michelin-pilot-sx-slick-bmx-tire-racing-654x420.jpg 654w\"></a></p><p>The Michelin Pilot SX has the deeper tread pattern, more suited to racing softer tracks in colder climes. The bigger lugs mean it offers extra grip while cornering, particularly on hard-packed or dusty terrain.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102318/michelin-bmx-tires-pilot-sx-casing.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102318/michelin-bmx-tires-pilot-sx-casing.jpg\" alt=\"michelin bmx tires pilot casing\" width=\"1200\" height=\"852\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102318/michelin-bmx-tires-pilot-sx-casing.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102318/michelin-bmx-tires-pilot-sx-casing.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102318/michelin-bmx-tires-pilot-sx-casing-297x211.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102318/michelin-bmx-tires-pilot-sx-casing-800x568.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102318/michelin-bmx-tires-pilot-sx-casing-120x85.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102318/michelin-bmx-tires-pilot-sx-casing-768x545.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102318/michelin-bmx-tires-pilot-sx-casing-696x494.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102318/michelin-bmx-tires-pilot-sx-casing-1068x758.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22102318/mi